### Create Admin User
POST http://localhost:8000/user/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@mermaid.com",
  "password": "AdminPassword123!",
  "admin": true,
  "profilePicture": ""
}

###

### Create Regular User
POST http://localhost:8000/user/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "password": "UserPassword123!",
  "admin": false,
  "profilePicture": ""
}

###

### Login
POST http://localhost:8000/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@mermaid.com",
  "password": "AdminPassword123!"
}

###

### Get User Info (requires token)
GET http://localhost:8000/user
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Confirm Email (replace TOKEN with actual token from email)
GET http://localhost:8000/user/confirm/TOKEN

###

### Delete User (Direct Database Query - Run in PostgreSQL)
# Connect to your PostgreSQL database and run:
# DELETE FROM "Users" WHERE email = 'admin@admin.com';
# or
# DELETE FROM "Users" WHERE id = 1;

